#week-title("Three", "Circulating the Waters")

=== Core Teaching

The final stage of preparing the Philosophic Mercury is the circulation. Once
the water has been fermented and distilled, its volatile fraction is cohobated
back over the residual salt and circulated.

This week, compare your cohobated rainwater with plain distilled water. Use
your senses: Is there a difference in visual "vitality," scent, or "feel" on
the skin? This comparison is its own teaching on the nature of the
potentized spirit.

#lab[
  *Circulation Protocol*
  + *Distillation:* Distil the fermented rainwater and collect the volatile fraction.
  + *Cohobation:* Pour the volatile fraction back over the residual salt.
  + *Sensory Analysis:* Compare the result with plain distilled water. Note the
    differences in your journal.
]

=== Topics This Week

- Cohobating the spirit back over the salt of water
- Sensory differences between dead and living water
- Circulation as a method of intensification

#inner-work[
  *The Circulation of Vitality*

  Focus on the feeling of vitality in your own body this week. Can you
  distinguish between "heavy" energy and "vital" energy?

  Practice the Threefold Breath and imagine the "circulation" of your inner
  Mercury, Sulphur, and Salt. Record how this awareness changes your sense of
  presence in the laboratory.
]

